### 3. **Computational Overhead**  
Every extra **granularity** comes at a **cost**: more memory, more processing cycles, and, inevitably, more **complexity**.  The **computational complexity** of an algorithm that operates on **fine‑grained** data can balloon from **O(n)** to **O(n²)** or worse, especially when naive **nested loops** are employed to handle each tiny sub‑task.  

